TYT did a segment in which they claimed that the C-Star was assisted by the Sea-Eye. This is incorrect. The Sea-Eye was prepared to assist but in the end it wasn't necessary. Altering these small stories to advance a narrative takes away from your coverage of larger issues. The fact that the Sea-Eye was prepared to assist is just as powerful as it actually doing so. It raises the question of whether or not to trust your reporting in other instances. If you're going to report on these stories, please ensure it's accurate to maintain the standard of reporting that your audience expects. I'll continue to be a fan of TYT, but these instances are disappointing and muddy the waters of all of your reporting integrity.
